participating-org.narrative:
1. The Company may raise capital in the following cases:
a) Increase in capital contributed by a member;
b) Receiving of capital contributed by new members. 2. In case of capital increase in the capital contributed by members, the increased contributedcapital is divided by members in proportion corresponding to their contributed capital in the charter capital of the Company. Members may transfer of such contributed capital to others as stipulated in Article 53 of the Law on Enterprises (2014). Any member in opposition to the decision on increase of the charter capital might not contribute additional capital. In this case, such additional capital of the members shall be allocated to other members in proportion corresponding to their contributed capitalin the charter capital of the Company unless otherwise agreed among the members.
3. The Company may decrease its Charter capital in the following forms:
a) Refundof capital contribution for a member in proportion corresponding to his/her capital contributions in the charter capital of the Company in case of continuous operation of business for over two years from the date of business registration; at the same time, it is required to ensure the payment of all debts and other financial obligations afterrefund for such member;
b) Redemption of capital contribution of a member by the Company as specified in Article 52 of the Law on Enterprises (2014);
c) The capital is not paid by members in full and on time as stipulated in Article 48 of the Law on Enterprises (2014).
4. Within ten (10) working days from the dateof completion the increase or decrease in the charter capital, the Company is required to notify in writing to the Business Registration Agency. The notice must contain the following main particulars:
a) Name, Headquarter, company prefix;
b) The charter capital; planned capital increase or decrease;
c) Time, reason and form of capital increase or decrease;
d) Full name and signature of the legal representative of the enterprise.
6
Withregard to increase in charter capital, resolutions and minute of meetings of the Councilof Members shall be attached to the notice. With regard to increase in charter capital, resolutions and minute of meetings of the Council of Members and the most recent financial statements of the Company shall be attached to the notice. Business Registration Agency shall update the increase or decrease of the charter capital within three (03) working days from the date of receiving the notice.
